name: curr_bw
doc: Sets the bandwidth for AC current measurements.

name: curr_null_enable
doc: Enables or disables the null function for AC or DC current measurements

name: curr_null_value
doc: Sets the null value for AC or DC current measurements

name: curr_null_value_auto
doc: Sets the null value for AC or DC current measurements

name: curr_range
doc: Selects a fixed measurement range for AC or DC current measurements on the 3 A terminals.

name: curr_range_auto
doc: Disables or enables autoranging for AC or DC current measurements. Auto-ranging is convenient because it automatically selects the range for each measurement based on the input signal. Did not implement ONCE

name: curr_nplc
doc: Sets the integration time in number of power line cycles (PLC) for DC current measurements. Integration time is the period that the instruments analog-to digital (A/D) converter samples the input signal for a measurement. A longer integration time gives better measurement resolution but slower measurement speed.

name: curr_res
doc: Selects the measurement resolution for DC current measurements. Specify the resolution in the same units as the selected measurement function, not in number of digits.

name: meas_cap
doc:
Sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for capacitance measurements
and immediately triggers a measurement. The results are sent directly to the instrument's output
buffer.

name: meas_curr
doc: Sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for AC or DC current measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. The results are sent directly to the instruments output buffer.

name: meas_volt
doc: Sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for AC or DC voltage measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. The results are sent directly to the instruments output buffer.

name: hardcopy_format
doc: Set the image format for the hardcopy command

name: hardcopy
doc: Returns an image of the screen

name: volt_range
doc: Set the range of voltage measurements, Auto is also an option

name: volt_range_auto
doc: Turn on or off auto ranging

name: volt_autozero_dc
doc: Turn on or off auto zero; only valid for DC

name: volt_aperture
doc: Acquisition aperture, use NPLC for better power-line rejection

name: sample_timer
doc: Sets a sample interval for timed sampling

name: sample_source
doc: Imm: trigger delay inserted after completion of each measurement; 'TIM': deterministic time between samples

name: sample_count
doc: Number of samples per trigger

name: sample_count_pretrigger
doc: Number of pre-trigger samples

name: trig_slope
doc: Slope of external trigger

name: trig_source
doc: Trigger source

name: trig_delay
doc: Delay after trigger before the first measurement

name: trig_count
doc: Number of triggers before returning to idle. Continuous (specified by INF) is also possible

name: read_error
doc: Get an error from the communication module

name: initialize
doc: Initialize measurement

name: fetch
doc: Get data in buffer

name: data_pts
doc: query the number of data points in memory

name: data_pts_threshold
doc: Set a threshold of data available for setting of status bit before setting bit 9 in the Standard Operation Register group event register to 1

name: store_data
doc: store readings to a file

name: upload_data
doc: upload file data to the host computer

name: trig
doc: Trigger via Bus

name: id
doc: Get instrument id

name: comm_error
doc: Get an error from the communication module.  True if Error

name: comm_error_details
doc: Get an error from the communication module.  Return the full string

name: reset
doc: Reset

name: operation_complete
doc: Returns 1 if init operation is complete

name: burst_volt
doc: configures a burst read of voltages

name: burst_volt_timer
doc: configures a burst read of voltages that are timed

name: clear_status
doc: clear the event register in all register groups
